#Text=Why have you chosen to involve yourself in the political process ?
#Text=Great communities , like great cities , are built from shared dreams that address shared needs .
#Text=I have been a Councillor for the last 15 years , and I am proud to have helped guide the growth and improvement of our community .
#Text=In the last few years , we have seen the neighbourhoods in St. Paul 's West increase in recognition , reputation and property value .
#Text=This has not occurred by chance .
#Text=I have worked hard to build successful , creative and vibrant relationships amongst local , corporate and government stakeholders in order to stimulate local renewal and make it happen !
#Text=We are on the cusp of a renaissance on St. Clair that will reap tremendous rewards for small business and residents .

#Text=Millions of dollars of City investment in street and transit improvements ; support for local Business Improvement Areas ; the Wychwood Barns Park ; the upgrading of our play parks , the Cedarvale Ravine and the Kay Gardner Beltline Park ; all this work is making Ward 21 a wonderful place to live and raise families .
#Text=I have a vision of community and City growth - one that is sustainable , civil and inclusive .
#Text=I enjoy working with people who have a passion for this community and City .
#Text=This is why I am involved in the political process .
#Text=Why do you want to represent this particular ward on council ?
#Text=The creativity , passion and positive community spirit of residents and businesses in Ward 21 , St. Paul 's West , continues to inspire me .
#Text=It has made my work as city Councillor , a real pleasure .
#Text=Together , we are transforming our neighbourhood and our City into one that works - because we are addressing our shared needs , hopes and aspirations , in a fair and equitable manner .
#Text=How are you currently involved in the community ?
#Text=My recent involvements include :
#Text=Salsa on St. Clair , a street festival to showcase both Hillcrest Village businesses & Latin culture ;
#Text=Melitaville Festival to support community engagement in Davenport-Shaw neighbourhood
#Text=St. Clair
#Text=Art Walk to showcase local artists with Wychwood Heights businesses
#Text=transformation of the TTC Wychwood Car Barns into a Park to provide valuable green space , recreation , live/work : * space for artists , and community space
#Text=protected banks of Cedarvale Ravine which led to a City-wide ravine protection by-law
#Text=annual Spring Clean-up Days in Cedarvale and Nordheimer Ravines , and Kay Gardner Beltline Park

#Text=support for the West Toronto Initiative for Solar Energy ( WISE ) to purchase solar systems for the roofs of interested community members , reduce household-produced emissions and contribute to sustainable energy .
#Text=a home for the heritage Tollkeepers Cottage at Bathurst and Davenport ; and , restoration of the historic Connaught Gates
#Text=fought the demolition of rental units at 310/320 Tweedsmuir Ave , which led to new City zoning laws restricting condo conversions of rental housing stock
#Text=stopped the McDonald 's drive-thru on St. Clair which led to City by-law prohibiting drive-thrus near residentially-zoned areas
#Text=improved playground equipment in Graham Park , Marian Engel Park , Humewood Park , Cawthra Park , and park infrastructure in the Kay Gardner Beltline and Cedarvale Park ;
#Text=Wall murals by local artists to improve neglected lands
#Text=the merger of Upper Village ( Toronto ) and Upper Village ( York )
#Text=BIAs
#Text=Forest Hill Village
#Text=BIA 's " Village Vision " began to renew the face of the retail village
